to address scientific, environmental and societal problems. Students and faculty work side-by-side in UNT’s 51 centers and institutes to advance knowledge and improve society. The Office of the Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs (VPAA) is responsible for the centers and institutes, 82% of which are research-focused. Mission: The Office of the Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs is responsible for the main mission of the institution including teaching, research and service. The Provost's office provides leadership in the development and supervision of the university’s academic programs in conjunction with the deans and representatives of the faculty in the following areas: changes in curriculum degree programs organization Provost Vice Provosts Deans & Associate-Deans Chairs Additional Academic Leadership Provost Office Staff Academic and Reporting Structure View our People Directory » Organization of Academic Affairs The numerous activities of Academic Affairs can be found in the many ‘neighborhoods’ located throughout campus. Academic Resources Faculty Success International Affairs Student Success UNT Career Connect (QEP) For more information, please contact us. Visit Us   Office of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs370 Hurley Administration Building Mail Us   University of North TexasOffice of the Provost and VP for Academic Affairs 1155 Union Circle #311190 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 [map]   Contact Us   940-565-2550 TTY: 940-369-8652 FAX: 940-565-2774 For questions about this website, contact ronda.bewley@unt.edu   Site last updated on: May 09, 2017 Disclaimer  |  AA/EOE/ADA  |  Privacy  |   Electronic Accessibility  |  State of Texas Online  |  Emergency Preparedness  |  THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information  |  UNT Compliance Hotline  |  Governors Committee on People with Disabilities  |  Texas Veterans Portal  |  UNT Home 